<div class="innerpage">
    <h1>why explorers early learning?</h1>
    <p class="heading">
        The Explorers values, Code of Conduct, Early Childhood Australia’s 
                Code of Ethics and the UN Convention
        <br>
        on the rights of the child, guide 
                the practices and attitudes of the Explorers Team.
    </p>

    <div class="infobox">
        <h2>Our Children</h2>
        <ul class="listing">
            <li>
                <div class="list">1.1</div>
                <div class="text">
                    Children are seen as active participants in creating their own 
                    learning environment within a safe indoor/outdoor program that fosters 
                    their well-being and development.
                </div>
            </li>

            <li>
                <div class="list">1.2</div>
                <div class="text">
                    A child initiated play based program stimulates 
                    children’s learning, exploration and social connections.
                </div>
            </li>

            <li>
                <div class="list">1.3</div>
                <div class="text">Children are trusted to make choices.</div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <div class="list">1.4</div>
                <div class="text">Children are recognised as a competent community of teachers and learners.</div>
            </li>

        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="infobox">
        <h2>Our Families</h2>
        <ul class="listing">
            <li>
                <div class="list">2.1</div>
                <div class="text">Families are the primary influence on their child’s learning and development.</div>
            </li>

            <li>
                <div class="list">2.2</div>
                <div class="text">Respectful partnerships between educators and each family are nurtured and valued.</div>
            </li>

            <li>
                <div class="list">2.3</div>
                <div class="text">
                    Children are given the opportunity to spend quality time with siblings, 
                    family and friends.
                </div>
            </li>

            <li>
                <div class="list">2.4</div>
                <div class="text">
                    All families have the opportunity to discuss the development and 
                    well-being of their children in a professional and confidential environment.
                </div>
            </li>

        </ul>
    </div>


    <div class="infobox">
        <h2>Our Staff</h2>
        <ul class="listing">
            <li>
                <div class="list">3.1</div>
                <div class="text">
                    Educators are intentional in their approach to 
                    creating meaningful opportunities for learning.
                </div>
            </li>

            <li>
                <div class="list">3.2</div>
                <div class="text">Educators explore and share diverse pedagogical practices and experiences.</div>
            </li>

            <li>
                <div class="list">3.3</div>
                <div class="text">
                    Explorers are dedicated to learning about and 
                    acknowledging the traditional owners of the land.
                </div>
            </li>

        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="infobox">
        <h2>Our Community</h2>
        <ul class="listing">
            <li>
                <div class="list">4.1</div>
                <div class="text">Exploring the local community allows children to develop their sense of belonging.</div>
            </li>

            <li>
                <div class="list">4.2</div>
                <div class="text">
                    The Explorers community is enriched by celebrating and sharing 
                    similarities and differences.
                </div>
            </li>

            <li>
                <div class="list">4.3</div>
                <div class="text">
                    Explorers are dedicated to learning about and 
                    acknowledging the traditional owners of the land.
                </div>
            </li>

        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="infobox">
        <h2>Our Environment</h2>
        <ul class="listing">
            <li>
                <div class="list">3.1</div>
                <div class="text">
                    Children are encouraged to explore their inherent 
                    connection to nature, including dirt,sand, and water.
                </div>
            </li>

            <li>
                <div class="list">3.2</div>
                <div class="text">
                    Children form empathy towards all living things through enjoyment 
                    of nature and asense of responsibility within quality environmental programs.
                </div>
            </li>

            <li>
                <div class="list">3.3</div>
                <div class="text">
                    The Explorers community are dedicated to promoting 
                    and implementing sustainablepractices, including edible gardens.
                </div>
            </li>

            <li>
                <div class="list">3.3</div>
                <div class="text">
                    Explorers promotes the use of recycled, reusable, natural 
                    and sustainable resources.
                </div>
            </li>

        </ul>

    </div>
    <div class="clear"></div>
    <p class="text2">A safe environment will be prioritised over any element of the philosophy, program or policy.</p>

